## Part 1 — Purpose and Scope

### 1.1 — What the Measure Catalog Is

The Measure Catalog is the single runtime reference target for equipment wattage assumptions in the Deepwalk Inference Engine. When Stage 9 needs `W_fixture` for an equipment cluster, it queries the catalog. The pipeline does not query external sources (DEER, ENERGY STAR, DLC, ASHRAE, or manufacturer databases) at runtime. Those sources feed a catalog maintenance process that runs separately. The catalog is always what the Inference Engine hits.

This architecture serves two goals. First, runtime performance — catalog lookups are fast and predictable; external source queries are not. Second, auditability — every wattage assumption used in a savings calculation is traceable to a specific versioned catalog entry with a known source and a known promotion history.

### 1.2 — Two Distinct Deliverables

This spec and the living catalog are separate deliverables with different owners and different update cadences. Conflating them is a persistent source of confusion and is explicitly prohibited.

| Deliverable | Document | Type | Location | Content |
|-------------|----------|------|----------|---------|
| This spec | `03_Measure_Catalog_Spec` | Tier 4 — Module Spec | Drive + GitHub `docs/modules/` | Ingestion rules, schema, version lifecycle, fallback hierarchy, IE interface contract |
| Living catalog | `02_Measure_Catalog` | Reference Library | Drive | Actual catalog entries — starts empty, populated through engagements and maintenance processes |

### 1.3 — Platform Extensibility

The catalog schema defined in this document is intentionally generic. No Deepwalk-specific concepts are baked into the schema. The `equipment_class` taxonomy is a Deepwalk-defined registry, but the schema that holds catalog entries can accommodate other use cases — other equipment domains, other external source mappings, other version workflows — without structural changes. This is a deliberate design constraint: the Discovery Studio toolset may be adapted for use cases beyond Deepwalk, and the catalog architecture must not foreclose that.

