## Part 3 — CatalogEntry Object Schema

Every entry in `02_Measure_Catalog` conforms to the following schema. Fields marked **Required** must be populated before an entry can advance beyond `Draft` status. Fields marked **Release-required** must be populated before an entry can advance to `Release` status.

```json
{
  "CatalogEntry": {
    "entry_id":                      "STRING    — UUID. Auto-generated at Draft creation.",
    "equipment_class":               "STRING    — UPPER_SNAKE_CASE. Must be ACTIVE in taxonomy registry. Required.",
    "display_name":                  "STRING    — Human-readable name for UI display and reports. Required.",
    "description":                   "STRING    — Plain-language definition of what this class covers and its boundaries. Required.",
    "w_fixture_w":                   "FLOAT     — Baseline wattage constant in watts. Release-required.",
    "w_fixture_source":              "STRING    — Source of the wattage value. See Part 5 for permitted values. Release-required.",
    "w_fixture_source_ref":          "STRING    — Citation, URL, document name, or database record ID. Release-required.",
    "w_fixture_confidence":          "ENUM      — LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH. Reflects source quality and specificity. Release-required.",
    "manufacturer":                  "STRING    — Optional. Populated when entry is manufacturer/model specific.",
    "model":                         "STRING    — Optional. Populated when entry is manufacturer/model specific.",
    "component_resolution_required": "BOOLEAN   — TRUE when sub-component detail materially affects w_fixture_w. Default: FALSE. See Part 6.",
    "component_note":                "STRING    — Optional. Populated when component_resolution_required is TRUE.",
    "auto_populated":                "BOOLEAN   — TRUE when created by the auto-populate process (Part 7, Step 3).",
    "ingestion_timestamp":           "TIMESTAMP — Set at entry creation. Immutable.",
    "source_type":                   "ENUM      — CUSTOMER_SUPPLIED / AUTO_POPULATED / MANUAL.",
    "catalog_version":               "STRING    — Semantic version of the catalog at time of Release. Null until Release.",
    "status":                        "ENUM      — DRAFT / COMMIT / RELEASE / DEPRECATED. See Part 4.",
    "promoted_by":                   "STRING    — Identity of the analyst who promoted to current status.",
    "promoted_at":                   "TIMESTAMP — Timestamp of most recent status promotion.",
    "changelog":                     "ARRAY     — Ordered log of all status changes and field edits. See Part 4.4.",
    "session_refs":                  "ARRAY OF STRINGS — Session IDs where this entry has been applied.",
    "notes":                         "STRING    — Optional. Free text for analyst commentary or audit notes."
  }
}
```

### Field-level rules

**`w_fixture_w`**
The wattage constant Stage 9 uses directly in the `P_load` calculation. Expressed in watts. Must reflect the baseline operational wattage of the equipment class at the specificity level of the entry — manufacturer/model specific when `manufacturer` and `model` are populated, class-level otherwise. Must be populated with a sourced, defensible value before `Release`.

**`w_fixture_confidence`**
Three levels. `HIGH` — manufacturer-specific data from a primary source (cut sheet, ENERGY STAR database, DLC listing). `MEDIUM` — class-level data from a recognized standard (DEER, ASHRAE). `LOW` — auto-populated from a secondary source or global catch-all default. Confidence level is surfaced in Inference Engine output and affects guarantee pool eligibility thresholds.

**`component_resolution_required`**
Set to `TRUE` when the class has sub-components whose variation materially affects `w_fixture_w` — for example, a fluorescent fixture where the wattage depends on ballast type, or a terminal unit where the load depends on coil configuration. When `TRUE`, the Inference Engine flags the observation for Enrichment Review if no component detail is available in the session record. Default is `FALSE`. See Part 6.

**`auto_populated`**
Set to `TRUE` when the entry was created by the Step 3 auto-populate process. Auto-populated entries are created at `Draft` status and routed to the catalog maintenance queue for human review. They must be promoted by an Analyst before reaching `Commit` or `Release`.

**`ingestion_timestamp`**
Set at entry creation. Immutable. The primary field enabling efficient catalog maintenance — entries can be sorted and filtered by ingestion date to identify stale assumptions, prioritize review, and track catalog growth over time.

**`session_refs`**
Populated by the Inference Engine each time an entry is applied to a session. Enables downstream impact assessment when an entry is revised — any session in `session_refs` may need recalculation if `w_fixture_w` changes between the version used and the current version.

