## Part 4 — Version Control Lifecycle

### 4.1 — Status States

Every catalog entry exists in one of four states:

| Status | Meaning | May be used by IE? |
|--------|---------|-------------------|
| `DRAFT` | Entry created; under review; not yet validated | No |
| `COMMIT` | Entry reviewed and approved by Analyst; available for use in non-guarantee sessions | Yes — with `w_fixture_confidence` surfaced in output |
| `RELEASE` | Entry fully validated; available for use in all sessions including guarantee calculations | Yes |
| `DEPRECATED` | Entry retired; no longer available for new sessions; historical records preserved | No — historical only |

### 4.2 — Promotion Rules

**Draft → Commit**
Required: all Required fields populated. `w_fixture_w` populated with a sourced value (even if `w_fixture_confidence` is `LOW`). Promoted by an Analyst. Changelog entry recorded.

**Commit → Release**
Required: all Release-required fields populated. `w_fixture_confidence` must be `MEDIUM` or `HIGH` — `LOW` confidence entries may not reach `Release`. Promoted by an Analyst with Third Switch review sign-off. Changelog entry recorded. `catalog_version` assigned.

**Release → Deprecated**
Required: a replacement entry at `Release` status exists for the same `equipment_class` (unless the class itself is being deprecated). Changelog entry recorded. All sessions in `session_refs` are flagged for review.

> **Note:** Auto-populated entries are created at `Draft` and follow the same promotion path. They may not be promoted by an automated process — Analyst review is required at every promotion step.

### 4.3 — Catalog Versioning

The catalog as a whole is versioned using semantic versioning (`MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`). A new catalog version is issued when one or more entries are promoted to `Release`. Facilitator pre-session configuration references a specific `catalog_version`, locking the wattage assumptions for that session at the time of configuration. Session records preserve the `catalog_version` used, ensuring historical calculations remain reproducible.

**Version increment rules:**

| Increment | Trigger |
|-----------|---------|
| `PATCH` | Correction to an existing `Release` entry that does not change `w_fixture_w` (source citation update, display name correction, notes addition) |
| `MINOR` | New `equipment_class` key reaches `Release`, or `w_fixture_w` changes on an existing entry by less than 10% |
| `MAJOR` | `w_fixture_w` changes on an existing entry by 10% or more, or an `equipment_class` key is deprecated |

### 4.4 — Changelog Object

Every status promotion and every field edit on a `Commit` or `Release` entry is recorded in the entry's `changelog` array. The changelog is append-only.

```json
{
  "ChangelogEntry": {
    "change_id":      "STRING    — UUID. Auto-generated.",
    "timestamp":      "TIMESTAMP — Immutable. System-generated.",
    "changed_by":     "STRING    — Analyst identity.",
    "action":         "ENUM      — CREATED / PROMOTED / FIELD_EDIT / DEPRECATED.",
    "from_status":    "ENUM      — Previous status. Null for CREATED.",
    "to_status":      "ENUM      — New status. Null for FIELD_EDIT.",
    "field_changed":  "STRING    — Field name. Populated for FIELD_EDIT only.",
    "previous_value": "STRING    — Previous field value. Populated for FIELD_EDIT only.",
    "new_value":      "STRING    — New field value. Populated for FIELD_EDIT only.",
    "rationale":      "STRING    — Required for PROMOTED and FIELD_EDIT on Release entries. Optional otherwise."
  }
}
```

