## Part 5 — External Source Ingestion Rules

### 5.1 — Supported External Sources

The following external sources are supported for catalog entry population. These sources are never queried by the Inference Engine directly — they feed the catalog through the auto-populate process (Part 7, Step 3) or through manual Analyst ingestion.

| Source | Type | `w_fixture_confidence` | Notes |
|--------|------|----------------------|-------|
| Manufacturer cut sheet | Primary | `HIGH` | Specific to manufacturer and model. Requires `manufacturer` and `model` fields populated. |
| ENERGY STAR database | Primary | `HIGH` | Product-level certified data. Requires model number match. |
| DLC (DesignLights Consortium) | Primary | `HIGH` | Product-level certified data for lighting. Requires DLC listing number. |
| DEER | Deemed | `MEDIUM` | California jurisdiction. Class-level deemed values. DEER version must be recorded in `w_fixture_source_ref`. |
| ASHRAE / building vintage standard | Standard | `MEDIUM` | Class-level defaults by building type and vintage. ASHRAE edition must be recorded in `w_fixture_source_ref`. |
| Customer-supplied inventory | Customer | `MEDIUM`–`HIGH` | Fixture schedules, cut sheets, equipment inventories from Scoping or Enrichment. Source provenance recorded. `MEDIUM` unless corroborated by a primary source. |

> **External source query priority** — when the auto-populate process queries external sources, the query priority among supported sources is engagement-configurable. This spec names the supported sources; it does not rank them. Priority order is set in Facilitator pre-session configuration and may be negotiated with the customer or sponsor.

### 5.2 — Ingestion Field Mapping

When an external source value is ingested into a catalog entry, the following fields must be populated at ingestion time:

| CatalogEntry field | What to record |
|-------------------|---------------|
| `w_fixture_w` | The wattage value from the source, in watts |
| `w_fixture_source` | The source name (e.g., `DEER`, `ENERGY_STAR`, `MANUFACTURER_CUT_SHEET`) |
| `w_fixture_source_ref` | The specific citation — URL, database record ID, document name, DEER measure ID, ASHRAE edition and table reference |
| `w_fixture_confidence` | Per the table in Part 5.1 |
| `source_type` | `AUTO_POPULATED` if created by auto-populate process; `MANUAL` if created by Analyst; `CUSTOMER_SUPPLIED` if sourced from customer-submitted inventory |
| `ingestion_timestamp` | System-generated at entry creation. Immutable. |
| `auto_populated` | `TRUE` if auto-populate process; `FALSE` if manual |

### 5.3 — Customer-Supplied Inventory

Customer-supplied inventory (fixture schedules, cut sheets, equipment inventories submitted during Scoping or Enrichment Review) is ingested as a catalog source like any other. It does not create session-level overrides — it feeds the catalog, and the catalog is what the Inference Engine queries.

Source provenance is always recorded. The `w_fixture_source_ref` field records the customer engagement and document reference so that the entry can be enriched with a higher-quality source over time, and so that audit challenges can be addressed without ambiguity about where the value came from.

Customer-supplied data is assigned `w_fixture_confidence = MEDIUM` unless corroborated by a primary source (manufacturer cut sheet, ENERGY STAR, or DLC listing), in which case confidence may be elevated to `HIGH` by the Analyst at promotion time.

