## Part 7 — Wattage Fallback Hierarchy

This is the formal lookup sequence the Inference Engine must follow when resolving `W_fixture` for an equipment cluster. Steps are executed in order. The first step that produces a result terminates the sequence.

### Step 1 — Catalog exact match

Query `02_Measure_Catalog` for a `RELEASE`-status entry matching `equipment_class` + `manufacturer` + `model`. If found, use `w_fixture_w` from that entry. Record `catalog_entry_id` and `catalog_version` in the session record. Terminate sequence.

### Step 2 — Catalog class-level match

No exact match found. Query `02_Measure_Catalog` for a `RELEASE`-status entry matching `equipment_class` only (no manufacturer/model constraint). If found, use `w_fixture_w` from that entry. Record `catalog_entry_id`, `catalog_version`, and flag `class_level_match = TRUE` in the session record. Terminate sequence.

A `COMMIT`-status entry may be used at this step when no `RELEASE` entry exists, subject to the constraint that `COMMIT`-status wattage values are excluded from guarantee pool calculations. The output record must surface the entry status.

### Step 3 — Auto-populate from external source

No catalog match at any level. The system queries the configured external sources in the engagement-specified priority order (see Part 5.1). On first match:

- `w_fixture_w` is extracted from the source
- A new `CatalogEntry` is created in `02_Measure_Catalog` at `DRAFT` status with `auto_populated = TRUE`, `source_type = AUTO_POPULATED`, `ingestion_timestamp` set, and all available source fields populated per Part 5.2
- The new entry is routed to the catalog maintenance queue for Analyst review and promotion
- The value is used for the current session with `auto_populated = TRUE` and `w_fixture_confidence = LOW` flagged in the session record
- The entry is excluded from guarantee pool calculations pending promotion to `COMMIT` or `RELEASE`

If no external source match is found across all configured sources, proceed to Step 4.

### Step 4 — Global catch-all

No catalog match and no external source match. The system assigns the minimum wattage value for the equipment class from an internal defaults table. Flags applied to the session record: `is_default_applied = TRUE`, `w_fixture_source = CATCH_ALL`, `w_fixture_confidence = LOW`. The observation is routed to Enrichment Review with a `WATTAGE_UNRESOLVED` flag. The value is excluded from guarantee pool calculations. No catalog entry is written until the value is manually confirmed by an Analyst.

